metadata.name: Inertia #632
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.name: Bougainvillea #233
Shapes #10
metadata.description:
While I was waiting for my turn in a doctor appointment, I saw a 'geometric-ish' framed art hanged in the wall of the waiting room. Those piece was so simple, but in the same time so elegant and this have inspired me a bit. So, I decided to make something similar using javascript, but with the fancy touch of randomization, tks to fxrand() function.

The supply is medium but the price is promotion.
Made with love.

D.
__________________________________
May 2022.

metadata.name: Code 1337 #3
metadata.description:
:> Project: Code 1337
:> Mission: Disseminate information
:> Objective: Provide dedicated time of valuable resource to as many as possible
:> Maturity: Experimental
:> Resource Identified: codecrafting
:> Project Brief:

Project Code 1337 will distribute 1337 generative line-art tokens to the general public. Tokens will contain the following features:

- Number of Lines: 25 - 100
- Number of Minutes: 5 (88.9%) | 30 (10%) | 60 (1%) | 120 (0.1%)
- Brush: Circle (50%) | Square (50%)
- Background: Dark (99%) | Light (1%)
- Has Noise: false (85%) | true (15%)

The project mission and objective will be carried out via the Number of Minutes feature. This value represents the number of dedicated minutes that the token owner can request from the identified resource.

Minutes may be used for consulting, advising, development, chatting, listening, questions, cups of coffee, silliness, etc. Minutes may not be used for illicit activity. Minutes may be combined. All tokens exchanged for used-minutes will be burned and cannot be used again.

All minutes must be scheduled with codecrafting via one of the means provided at cclabs.tech (twitter, discord, telegram). codecrafting will do his best to please but is not responsible for disappointment in the outcome of minutes.
